<p>You can also use the <a href="http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/generated/pandas.option_context.html" rel="noreferrer">option_context</a>, with one or more options:</p>

<pre><code>with pd.option_context('display.max_rows', None, 'display.max_columns', 3):
    print(df)
</code></pre>

<p>This will automatically return the options to their previous values.</p>

<p><strong>Addition</strong>:
If you are working on jupyter-notebook, using <code>display</code> instead of <code>print</code> will use jupyter rich display logic.</p>
